The site overview page went through a few iterations before the final design. After contextual interviews and learning more about the users, it became clear that this overview was not a fitting display for all user groups. Two main user types and contexts for the platform emerged: there were the Engineers, and the General Consumers.
<br>
<br>
Engineers were a technically-savvy user that wanted transparency of important sensor information in order to assess the health of the system and diagnose a problem, as well as a historical view of data, and the ability to look at isolated sensor point data.
